WEBVTT

1
00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:38.750
NARRATOR: The oldest stories ever told

2
00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:38.750
are written in the stars.

3
00:00:40.120 --> 00:00:45.920
Stories of time before man and gods,

4
00:00:40.120 --> 00:00:45.920
when Titans ruled the earth.

5
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.510
The Titans were powerful...

6
00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:51.720
...but their reign was ended

7
00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:51.720
by their own sons...

8
00:00:51.890 --> 00:00:56.890
...Zeus, Poseidon and Hades.

9
00:00:58.690 --> 00:01:00.480
Zeus convinced his brother Hades...

10
00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:04.610
...to create a beast so strong

11
00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:04.610
it could defeat their parents.

12
00:01:04.770 --> 00:01:06.650
And from his own flesh...

13
00:01:06.820 --> 00:01:11.200
...Hades gave birth

14
00:01:06.820 --> 00:01:11.200
to an unspeakable horror...

15
00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:13.280
...the Kraken.

16
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.540
Zeus became king of the heavens.

17
00:01:24.340 --> 00:01:27.800
Poseidon, king of the seas.

18
00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:31.340
And Hades, tricked by Zeus...

19
00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:36.760
...was left to rule the underworld

20
00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:36.760
in darkness and in misery.

21
00:01:38.810 --> 00:01:41.270
It was Zeus who created man...

22
00:01:41.440 --> 00:01:45.610
...and man's prayers

23
00:01:41.440 --> 00:01:45.610
fed the gods' immortality.

24
00:01:48.860 --> 00:01:52.860
But in time, mankind grew restless.

25
00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:55.160
They began to question the gods...

26
00:01:55.330 --> 00:01:59.370
...and, finally, rise up against them.

27
00:02:05.750 --> 00:02:09.340
Into this world, a child was born.

28
00:02:10.260 --> 00:02:13.050
A boy who would change everything.

29
00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:36.070
[BABY CRYING]

30
00:02:44.210 --> 00:02:46.000
Shh. Shh.

31
00:02:50.250 --> 00:02:52.130
Perseus.

32
00:03:23.450 --> 00:03:25.290
What is it, son?

33
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.040
I'll have a brother or a sister soon.

34
00:03:30.130 --> 00:03:34.340
Think we're gonna love this child differently

35
00:03:30.130 --> 00:03:34.340
to the way we love you? We won't.

36
00:03:35.630 --> 00:03:37.680
This child will be yours.

37
00:03:37.840 --> 00:03:39.510
Me...

38
00:03:40.180 --> 00:03:41.390
...I'm no one's son.

39
00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:44.980
I am your father, Perseus.

40
00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:44.980
Marmara is your mother.

41
00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:48.940
And you'll always be our son.

42
00:03:49.690 --> 00:03:53.860
The bond between us

43
00:03:49.690 --> 00:03:53.860
is much more than flesh and bone.

44
00:03:54.320 --> 00:03:55.950
The love we have for you...

45
00:03:56.110 --> 00:04:00.990
...it's that love that gods and kings

46
00:03:56.110 --> 00:04:00.990
fight over.

47
00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:03.540
I've never understood the gods.

48
00:04:03.700 --> 00:04:06.540
But even I don't question

49
00:04:03.700 --> 00:04:06.540
that you were saved for a reason.

50
00:04:07.210 --> 00:04:09.000
And some day...

51
00:04:09.170 --> 00:04:14.340
...that reason is gonna take you

52
00:04:09.170 --> 00:04:14.340
far away from here.

53
00:04:15.670 --> 00:04:16.840
But not tonight, eh?

54
00:04:37.530 --> 00:04:39.990
SPYROS:

55
00:04:37.530 --> 00:04:39.990
Perseus. Perseus!

56
00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:42.370
Getting frail, old man.

57
00:04:42.530 --> 00:04:45.120
Marmara! Marmara!

58
00:04:49.710 --> 00:04:53.250
Another day, nothing.

59
00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:56.010
Caught on the reef.

60
00:04:56.170 --> 00:04:59.550
To whom do I direct our gratitude

61
00:04:56.170 --> 00:04:59.550
for this glorious bounty?

62
00:04:59.720 --> 00:05:01.010
Spyros, please.

63
00:05:01.180 --> 00:05:04.430
Poseidon, Zeus?

64
00:05:01.180 --> 00:05:04.430
Who do I thank, Marmara?

65
00:05:04.600 --> 00:05:07.430
- Thank the men who provoke them.

66
00:05:04.600 --> 00:05:07.430
SPYROS: They crush my island.

67
00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:09.730
They put a plague on yours.

68
00:05:09.890 --> 00:05:12.440
They take from us what they want.

69
00:05:09.890 --> 00:05:12.440
We're their slaves.

70
00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:14.070
The gods gave us life.

71
00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:18.820
-For that, we should be thankful.

72
00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:18.820
-I'm tired of being thankful for scraps.

73
00:05:18.990 --> 00:05:21.530
I'm a fisherman. Perseus is a fisherman.

74
00:05:21.700 --> 00:05:24.990
They've even taken that away from us.

75
00:05:21.700 --> 00:05:24.990
What we are.

76
00:05:25.490 --> 00:05:27.450
Still they want us to love them anyway.

77
00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:29.790
One day...

78
00:05:29.960 --> 00:05:32.420
...somebody's gonna have to

79
00:05:29.960 --> 00:05:32.420
make a stand.

80
00:05:32.580 --> 00:05:34.920
One day, somebody's gonna have to say:

81
00:05:35.090 --> 00:05:36.380
"Enough."

82
00:05:44.760 --> 00:05:46.970
[THUNDER CRASHING]

83
00:06:07.790 --> 00:06:10.410
Just like the day you came to me.

84
00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:16.630
The storm brought me right to you.

85
00:06:22.380 --> 00:06:24.010
I know you have questions, son.

86
00:06:24.640 --> 00:06:26.970
I wish I had the answers.

87
00:06:31.890 --> 00:06:33.520
I have everything I need...

88
00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:35.560
...right here.

89
00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:40.780
Good night, son.

90
00:06:58.550 --> 00:07:00.630
PERSEUS:

91
00:06:58.550 --> 00:07:00.630
Hold her steady!

92
00:07:01.050 --> 00:07:02.550
Tekla, the wreath.

93
00:07:02.720 --> 00:07:04.260
Fetch the wreath.

94
00:07:04.510 --> 00:07:07.430
SPYROS:

95
00:07:04.510 --> 00:07:07.430
The statue of Zeus. Magnificent.

96
00:07:21.280 --> 00:07:22.360
Something isn't right.

97
00:07:23.700 --> 00:07:26.200
The soldiers, what are they doing?

98
00:07:26.370 --> 00:07:27.660
[SOLDIERS YELLING]

99
00:07:27.830 --> 00:07:29.700
[METAL CLANKING ON STONE]

100
00:07:30.750 --> 00:07:31.790
MAN 1:

101
00:07:30.750 --> 00:07:31.790
Come on!

102
00:07:31.950 --> 00:07:33.500
MAN 2:

103
00:07:31.950 --> 00:07:33.500
Lift it!

104
00:07:36.420 --> 00:07:37.790
PERSEUS:

105
00:07:36.420 --> 00:07:37.790
Hang on!

106
00:07:37.960 --> 00:07:39.670
[TEKLA SCREAMS]

107
00:07:44.220 --> 00:07:46.470
MAN 3:

108
00:07:44.220 --> 00:07:46.470
In the name of the king and queen!

109
00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:48.640
Who are they?

110
00:07:48.800 --> 00:07:50.720
Soldiers from Argos.

111
00:07:51.350 --> 00:07:53.390
MARMARA:

112
00:07:51.350 --> 00:07:53.390
What have they done?

113
00:07:53.560 --> 00:07:57.060
SPYROS: They've declared war.

114
00:07:53.560 --> 00:07:57.060
War against the gods.

115
00:08:06.700 --> 00:08:07.950
[SQUAWKING]

116
00:08:16.170 --> 00:08:17.880
[SOLDIERS YELLING]

117
00:08:19.210 --> 00:08:21.420
-Let's turn the boat around.

118
00:08:19.210 --> 00:08:21.420
SPYROS: No.

119
00:08:21.590 --> 00:08:23.010
Do nothing.

120
00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:29.760
MAN 4:

121
00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:29.760
Behind you!

122
00:08:45.070 --> 00:08:46.900
[TEKLA SCREAMS]

123
00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:53.370
PERSEUS:

124
00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:53.370
Hold on!

125
00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:01.000
MARMARA:

126
00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:01.000
Tekla.

127
00:09:01.170 --> 00:09:02.290
SPYROS:

128
00:09:01.170 --> 00:09:02.290
Where's the boy?

129
00:09:08.380 --> 00:09:10.140
Tekla!

130
00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:38.120
No!

131
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:42.000
SPYROS: Go!

132
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:42.000
-No!

133
00:09:53.010 --> 00:09:55.680
[GASPING]

134
00:09:56.770 --> 00:09:59.730
[GROANING]

135
00:10:03.940 --> 00:10:06.400
No!

136
00:10:08.860 --> 00:10:13.070
MAN 1: Zeus, you must bring an end

137
00:10:08.860 --> 00:10:13.070
to this. They attack our temples!

138
00:10:13.240 --> 00:10:15.870
MAN 2:

139
00:10:13.240 --> 00:10:15.870
Now they dare to desecrate Zeus' image.

140
00:10:16.040 --> 00:10:17.370
WOMAN:

141
00:10:16.040 --> 00:10:17.370
We could reach out to them.

142
00:10:17.540 --> 00:10:19.160
MAN 3: An accommodation could be made.

143
00:10:17.540 --> 00:10:19.160
A truce!

144
00:10:19.330 --> 00:10:21.120
No!

145
00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:27.590
I created them...

146
00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:31.840
...and they reward my love with defiance?

147
00:10:32.010 --> 00:10:34.300
There will be no truce.

148
00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:36.430
HADES:

149
00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:36.430
Finally.

150
00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:38.560
Some rage from you.

151
00:10:42.480 --> 00:10:43.850
How long has it been?

152
00:10:44.690 --> 00:10:46.230
How long, brother...

153
00:10:46.400 --> 00:10:49.190
...since you've seen my face?

154
00:10:50.190 --> 00:10:51.450
Hades.

155
00:10:57.830 --> 00:11:03.420
Endless years,

156
00:10:57.830 --> 00:11:03.420
I've watched from the underworld...

157
00:11:03.790 --> 00:11:08.750
...and saw your wrath

158
00:11:03.790 --> 00:11:08.750
tempered with love.

159
00:11:08.920 --> 00:11:11.260
You created them for one reason...

160
00:11:11.420 --> 00:11:16.800
...so their prayers

161
00:11:11.420 --> 00:11:16.800
would fuel our immortality.

162
00:11:16.970 --> 00:11:19.520
But you love them too well.

163
00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:21.180
They've grown strong.

164
00:11:21.350 --> 00:11:26.610
And now I am forced to rise

165
00:11:21.350 --> 00:11:26.610
because we are all threatened.

166
00:11:26.770 --> 00:11:28.690
What do you want, brother?

167
00:11:28.860 --> 00:11:31.780
Let me loose upon them.

168
00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:34.780
They will pray again...

169
00:11:34.950 --> 00:11:38.120
...and you will bathe in their awe

170
00:11:34.950 --> 00:11:38.120
and fear.

171
00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:41.200
And we will grow strong again.

172
00:11:41.370 --> 00:11:43.620
He belongs in the underworld, not here.

173
00:11:43.790 --> 00:11:46.080
You do not tell me where I belong.

174
00:11:48.290 --> 00:11:51.760
You say it is love that feeds us.

175
00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:55.510
But you depend on their love.

176
00:11:55.680 --> 00:11:58.470
I've only learned to live on their fear...

177
00:11:59.470 --> 00:12:01.020
...their pain.

178
00:12:01.180 --> 00:12:05.600
Zeus, our brother speaks the truth.

179
00:12:01.180 --> 00:12:05.600
Hear him.

180
00:12:11.900 --> 00:12:14.450
Go. Do what you will.

181
00:12:14.610 --> 00:12:15.990
Father, we need the mortals.

182
00:12:16.160 --> 00:12:17.490
ZEUS:

183
00:12:16.160 --> 00:12:17.490
No, Apollo.

184
00:12:17.660 --> 00:12:19.120
Hades is right.

185
00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:21.870
Their insolence has a price.

186
00:12:22.040 --> 00:12:26.000
Like children, they need to be

187
00:12:22.040 --> 00:12:26.000
reminded of the order of things.

188
00:12:26.170 --> 00:12:28.330
Set an example, brother.

189
00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:30.340
Turn them on each other...

190
00:12:31.250 --> 00:12:33.210
...and back into our arms.

191
00:13:14.760 --> 00:13:17.680
-Are we the last boat to come in?

192
00:13:14.760 --> 00:13:17.680
MAN 1: No, captain.

193
00:13:18.090 --> 00:13:20.050
You're the only one.

194
00:13:21.050 --> 00:13:22.600
Is he one of ours?

195
00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:25.390
No. We found him off Paxos

196
00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:25.390
amongst our dead.

197
00:13:25.560 --> 00:13:27.060
He was the only survivor.

198
00:13:27.230 --> 00:13:29.980
Let the palace figure out

199
00:13:27.230 --> 00:13:29.980
what to do with him.

200
00:13:30.480 --> 00:13:32.770
MAN 2:

201
00:13:30.480 --> 00:13:32.770
Squad by four!

202
00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:34.980
MAN 3:

203
00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:34.980
Go on.

204
00:13:36.400 --> 00:13:38.240
MAN 4:

205
00:13:36.400 --> 00:13:38.240
Because if we show the gods our love...

206
00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:40.700
...they shall show us love in return.

207
00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:40.700
They shall.

208
00:13:40.860 --> 00:13:43.410
They gave us the corn in the fields,

209
00:13:40.860 --> 00:13:43.410
the sun in the sky.

210
00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:45.160
These are all gifts given to us.

211
00:13:45.330 --> 00:13:47.660
Gifts can be taken away.

212
00:13:45.330 --> 00:13:47.660
This will be taken away...

213
00:13:47.830 --> 00:13:49.580
...if we do not pay love to our gods.

214
00:13:49.750 --> 00:13:53.460
If we do not, we stay in filth and misery,

215
00:13:49.750 --> 00:13:53.460
which we have brought upon ourselves.

216
00:13:53.630 --> 00:13:56.340
MAN 5: Move. Out of the way.

217
00:13:53.630 --> 00:13:56.340
PROKOPION: Our gods, we beg for the whip--

218
00:13:56.510 --> 00:13:59.380
The beauty and clarity of servitude.

219
00:13:59.720 --> 00:14:03.300
Man cannot rule man. You defy the gods

220
00:13:59.720 --> 00:14:03.300
and you will be punished.

221
00:14:26.120 --> 00:14:28.830
[MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:14:31.500 --> 00:14:34.420
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

223
00:14:43.470 --> 00:14:44.720
Is this all there is?

224
00:14:45.390 --> 00:14:47.930
GENERAL:

225
00:14:45.390 --> 00:14:47.930
We lost many men, Your Majesty...

226
00:14:48.100 --> 00:14:49.930
...but we have victory.

227
00:14:52.480 --> 00:14:55.690
To King Kepheus! To Queen Cassiopeia!

228
00:14:55.860 --> 00:14:57.570
[CROWD CHEERS]

229
00:14:59.530 --> 00:15:00.860
No.

230
00:15:04.820 --> 00:15:06.370
To you...

231
00:15:07.580 --> 00:15:09.040
...our mighty legion.

232
00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:13.960
Our heroes who have dared

233
00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:13.960
to strike a blow at the heart of Zeus!

234
00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:16.750
[CROWD CHEERS]

235
00:15:17.040 --> 00:15:19.050
The temples are burning.

236
00:15:19.210 --> 00:15:21.510
The statues have fallen.

237
00:15:21.670 --> 00:15:24.090
We have starved them of our prayers.

238
00:15:24.510 --> 00:15:25.760
Tonight...

239
00:15:25.930 --> 00:15:28.310
...after a generation of struggle...

240
00:15:28.470 --> 00:15:31.140
...the sun does not set over the ocean.

241
00:15:31.310 --> 00:15:34.600
It sets on Olympus itself.

242
00:15:34.900 --> 00:15:37.360
A new era has begun.

243
00:15:37.860 --> 00:15:40.360
The era of man!

244
00:15:40.530 --> 00:15:42.030
[CROWD CHEERS]

245
00:15:42.190 --> 00:15:44.070
That frown doesn't suit you, Andromeda.

246
00:15:44.240 --> 00:15:47.280
Have something to drink.

247
00:15:44.240 --> 00:15:47.280
You'll feel more lively.

248
00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:52.620
Andromeda.

249
00:16:02.550 --> 00:16:03.590
What's your name?

250
00:16:04.550 --> 00:16:05.590
Perseus.

251
00:16:07.590 --> 00:16:09.220
Take this.

252
00:16:09.680 --> 00:16:11.600
Please drink.

253
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:16.900
DRACO: Hands off.

254
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:16.900
CASSIOPEIA: Enough.

255
00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:19.900
Our daughter, the missionary.

256
00:16:21.940 --> 00:16:24.820
Have you seen what's happening

257
00:16:21.940 --> 00:16:24.820
out there?

258
00:16:25.400 --> 00:16:27.200
Have you even bothered to look?

259
00:16:27.700 --> 00:16:29.450
We serve as an inspiration.

260
00:16:29.620 --> 00:16:32.790
ANDROMEDA: Hundreds of our men

261
00:16:29.620 --> 00:16:32.790
have lost their lives...

262
00:16:33.250 --> 00:16:35.410
...yet we celebrate.

263
00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:39.000
You provoke the gods and you act

264
00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:39.000
as if there will be no consequence.

265
00:16:39.170 --> 00:16:41.170
Well, what do you want?

266
00:16:39.170 --> 00:16:41.170
Should we be afraid?

267
00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:45.510
Should we be trembling

268
00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:45.510
and soiling ourselves in fear?

269
00:16:45.670 --> 00:16:47.220
The gods need us.

270
00:16:47.380 --> 00:16:48.680
They need our worship.

271
00:16:49.600 --> 00:16:51.890
What do we need of them?

272
00:16:52.060 --> 00:16:54.640
-Look at my daughter.

273
00:16:52.060 --> 00:16:54.640
-Don't.

274
00:16:54.810 --> 00:16:57.850
What could be more divine than her face?

275
00:16:58.020 --> 00:17:00.560
More beautiful

276
00:16:58.020 --> 00:17:00.560
than all the women of Greece.

277
00:17:00.730 --> 00:17:05.320
More beautiful than Aphrodite herself.

278
00:17:00.730 --> 00:17:05.320
The Olympians should envy her.

279
00:17:05.490 --> 00:17:10.370
-We are the gods now.

280
00:17:05.490 --> 00:17:10.370
-My queen. You're making a spectacle.

281
00:17:10.530 --> 00:17:13.450
[CREATURE SQUAWKING IN DISTANCE]

282
00:17:17.790 --> 00:17:20.790
[WIND BLOWING]

283
00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:24.800
[CHATTERING]

284
00:17:55.500 --> 00:17:56.710
Interesting.

285
00:17:56.880 --> 00:17:58.880
You!

286
00:18:17.360 --> 00:18:21.160
You are specks of dust

287
00:18:17.360 --> 00:18:21.160
beneath our fingernails.

288
00:18:21.660 --> 00:18:24.620
Your very breath is a gift from Olympus.

289
00:18:24.780 --> 00:18:28.450
You have insulted powers

290
00:18:24.780 --> 00:18:28.450
beyond your comprehension.

291
00:18:29.040 --> 00:18:30.160
Who are you?

292
00:18:31.040 --> 00:18:34.460
I am Hades.

293
00:18:37.760 --> 00:18:39.050
Kneel.

294
00:18:47.220 --> 00:18:48.350
Not now, Perseus.

295
00:18:49.020 --> 00:18:50.310
You will have your chance.

296
00:18:56.860 --> 00:18:59.570
HADES:

297
00:18:56.860 --> 00:18:59.570
What do you know of beauty?

298
00:18:59.740 --> 00:19:02.700
What is more beautiful than death?

299
00:19:06.950 --> 00:19:10.330
Gaze upon me, mortal queen.

300
00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:21.510
ANDROMEDA: Mother.

301
00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:21.510
DRACO: Princess.

302
00:19:23.340 --> 00:19:25.140
[ANDROMEDA GRUNTS]

303
00:19:28.310 --> 00:19:29.930
HADES:

304
00:19:28.310 --> 00:19:29.930
In 10 days...

305
00:19:30.100 --> 00:19:33.310
...when the sun is eclipsed...

306
00:19:34.270 --> 00:19:36.770
...I will unleash the Kraken.

307
00:19:37.860 --> 00:19:40.110
Argos will be swept from the earth...

308
00:19:40.780 --> 00:19:43.450
...and all of you with it.

309
00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:46.870
Unless...

310
00:19:47.030 --> 00:19:50.080
...you sacrifice the princess...

311
00:19:50.240 --> 00:19:53.290
...you so foolishly compare to the gods.

312
00:19:53.460 --> 00:19:56.540
Only her blood will sate the Kraken...

313
00:19:56.710 --> 00:19:58.790
...and Zeus...

314
00:19:58.960 --> 00:20:02.800
...who you have so offended.

315
00:20:05.970 --> 00:20:08.550
Choose your penance, Argos.

316
00:20:08.720 --> 00:20:11.640
Destruction or sacrifice.

317
00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:13.930
This is the will of Zeus.

318
00:20:14.810 --> 00:20:18.980
The will of your father.

319
00:20:32.040 --> 00:20:35.160
HERMES:

320
00:20:32.040 --> 00:20:35.160
There is a demigod in Argos.

321
00:20:36.830 --> 00:20:39.040
That is impossible.

322
00:20:39.840 --> 00:20:41.210
He's yours.

323
00:20:42.210 --> 00:20:44.880
His name is Perseus.

324
00:20:45.050 --> 00:20:47.430
We could offer him sanctuary.

325
00:20:48.640 --> 00:20:51.010
Have I heard his prayers?

326
00:20:51.180 --> 00:20:54.350
This son knows no love for me.

327
00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:58.440
He's no different from any of the others

328
00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:58.440
who have turned their backs on us.

329
00:20:58.690 --> 00:21:02.530
DRACO:

330
00:20:58.690 --> 00:21:02.530
For the last time, demigod, speak!

331
00:21:02.900 --> 00:21:06.700
-I'm not a demigod.

332
00:21:02.900 --> 00:21:06.700
-Who are you? Why were you sent?

333
00:21:07.150 --> 00:21:08.490
I don't know.

334
00:21:10.450 --> 00:21:12.830
[GRUNTING]

335
00:21:16.370 --> 00:21:17.750
AMMON:

336
00:21:16.370 --> 00:21:17.750
I advise against this, sire.

337
00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.880
-He's not to be trusted.

338
00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.880
-What would you have me do? Draco.

339
00:21:24.420 --> 00:21:25.710
Leave him.

340
00:21:30.550 --> 00:21:32.260
Is it possible?

341
00:21:32.890 --> 00:21:35.680
If it's true you are the son of Zeus...

342
00:21:35.850 --> 00:21:37.730
...you can save us.

343
00:21:40.270 --> 00:21:41.770
You must save us.

344
00:21:41.940 --> 00:21:44.440
I can't save you. I'm just a man.

345
00:21:44.610 --> 00:21:48.240
My lord, as terrible as it is

346
00:21:44.610 --> 00:21:48.240
to utter the words...

347
00:21:48.400 --> 00:21:50.110
...a sacrifice is the only way.

348
00:21:50.280 --> 00:21:52.030
Don't even say the word.

349
00:21:52.200 --> 00:21:53.620
ANDROMEDA:

350
00:21:52.200 --> 00:21:53.620
He's right.

351
00:21:54.410 --> 00:21:56.700
No one should have to die for me.

352
00:21:57.830 --> 00:21:59.170
Let Perseus go.

353
00:22:00.210 --> 00:22:03.920
Sire, we need to get the princess

354
00:22:00.210 --> 00:22:03.920
out of the city now.

355
00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:06.920
-I'll find a place to hide her.

356
00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:06.920
-You can't hide from Hades.

357
00:22:07.090 --> 00:22:09.470
So says the bastard son of a god.

358
00:22:14.510 --> 00:22:16.220
My father...

359
00:22:17.100 --> 00:22:18.770
...was killed by a god.

360
00:22:20.020 --> 00:22:23.360
My mother, sister...

361
00:22:24.110 --> 00:22:27.820
...everyone I loved was killed by a god.

362
00:22:28.820 --> 00:22:30.820
I mend nets...

363
00:22:30.990 --> 00:22:32.950
...not wield a sword.

364
00:22:41.870 --> 00:22:44.500
So, demigod, you have a visitor.

365
00:22:45.920 --> 00:22:47.960
She says she knows you.

366
00:22:51.300 --> 00:22:54.220
My name is Io, Perseus.

367
00:22:55.010 --> 00:22:56.350
And how do you know me?

368
00:22:57.010 --> 00:22:58.890
I've watched you all your life.

369
00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:01.640
I guided you to your family.

370
00:23:05.270 --> 00:23:06.480
Are you a god?

371
00:23:06.650 --> 00:23:08.320
There are gods and there are men...

372
00:23:09.070 --> 00:23:11.990
...and there are those of us

373
00:23:09.070 --> 00:23:11.990
who are in between.

374
00:23:12.400 --> 00:23:13.450
Many years ago...

375
00:23:14.070 --> 00:23:17.240
...I refused a god's advance.

376
00:23:17.410 --> 00:23:19.410
I was cursed with agelessness.

377
00:23:20.160 --> 00:23:22.120
That's not much of a curse.

378
00:23:22.290 --> 00:23:25.540
I've lived for years

379
00:23:22.290 --> 00:23:25.540
watching my loved ones die.

380
00:23:26.170 --> 00:23:28.590
I imagine you're sympathetic

381
00:23:26.170 --> 00:23:28.590
to that plight.

382
00:23:33.590 --> 00:23:35.340
Is it true?

383
00:23:37.510 --> 00:23:39.100
Am I the son of Zeus?

384
00:23:40.180 --> 00:23:41.230
Yes.

385
00:23:42.980 --> 00:23:47.360
The story of your birth

386
00:23:42.980 --> 00:23:47.360
began with the rebellion of King Acrisius.

387
00:23:49.530 --> 00:23:54.570
Mankind had grown tired

388
00:23:49.530 --> 00:23:54.570
of the gods' mistreatment and cruelty.

389
00:23:55.240 --> 00:23:58.780
Acrisius led a siege on Olympus.

390
00:24:00.040 --> 00:24:01.410
It is said the other gods...

391
00:24:01.580 --> 00:24:05.370
...wanted to simply lay waste to Acrisius

392
00:24:01.580 --> 00:24:05.370
and his army...

393
00:24:05.540 --> 00:24:08.340
...but Zeus loved man too much.

394
00:24:08.500 --> 00:24:13.130
Instead, he chose to make an example

395
00:24:08.500 --> 00:24:13.130
of Acrisius.

396
00:24:14.430 --> 00:24:17.890
He disguised himself as the king...

397
00:24:18.050 --> 00:24:21.430
...and visited the chamber

398
00:24:18.050 --> 00:24:21.430
where the king's wife was sleeping.

399
00:24:21.600 --> 00:24:22.640
My king.

400
00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:33.860
Zeus?

401
00:24:36.200 --> 00:24:38.280
[SCREAMS]

402
00:24:40.200 --> 00:24:42.580
IO:

403
00:24:40.200 --> 00:24:42.580
Acrisius grew mad with rage.

404
00:24:43.290 --> 00:24:46.330
He ordered the execution of his wife...

405
00:24:46.500 --> 00:24:48.920
...and Zeus' newborn son.

406
00:24:55.260 --> 00:24:56.680
I curse you, Zeus.

407
00:24:56.840 --> 00:24:59.300
I deny you the body you soiled...

408
00:24:59.470 --> 00:25:01.390
...and the bastard child with it!

409
00:25:02.560 --> 00:25:04.890
[YELLS]

410
00:25:05.060 --> 00:25:06.770
No!

411
00:25:11.440 --> 00:25:14.070
[YELLING]

412
00:25:20.120 --> 00:25:23.330
The queen and her child

413
00:25:20.120 --> 00:25:23.330
were cast into the sea.

414
00:25:23.490 --> 00:25:25.540
Your mother was killed, but you...

415
00:25:25.700 --> 00:25:28.460
...part man, part god, you lived.

416
00:25:29.250 --> 00:25:31.130
I've watched over you ever since...

417
00:25:31.290 --> 00:25:35.340
...waiting for the day when you will help

418
00:25:31.290 --> 00:25:35.340
bring an end to the tyranny of the gods.

419
00:25:35.510 --> 00:25:38.720
You were born to kill the Kraken.

420
00:25:40.890 --> 00:25:43.430
I don't know why I was born...

421
00:25:44.810 --> 00:25:46.770
...or what I am.

422
00:25:48.690 --> 00:25:50.730
But I know it's not the Kraken

423
00:25:48.690 --> 00:25:50.730
I wanna kill.

424
00:25:51.520 --> 00:25:53.440
How do I get to Hades?

425
00:25:53.610 --> 00:25:55.650
If the Kraken falls...

426
00:25:55.820 --> 00:25:59.490
...Hades will be weak enough

427
00:25:55.820 --> 00:25:59.490
for you to strike a deathly blow.

428
00:25:59.660 --> 00:26:02.450
Only then will you have the revenge

429
00:25:59.660 --> 00:26:02.450
you seek.

430
00:26:02.620 --> 00:26:04.660
Then they better release me.

431
00:26:04.830 --> 00:26:05.910
[BANGING ON DOOR]

432
00:26:08.540 --> 00:26:10.370
IO:

433
00:26:08.540 --> 00:26:10.370
If the Kraken can be killed...

434
00:26:10.540 --> 00:26:12.750
...the Stygian witches will know how.

435
00:26:12.920 --> 00:26:15.710
The witches are further away

436
00:26:12.920 --> 00:26:15.710
than the legion has ever been.

437
00:26:15.880 --> 00:26:17.010
No man can go there.

438
00:26:17.170 --> 00:26:18.840
No man.

439
00:26:21.550 --> 00:26:23.680
Keep your distance, Io.

440
00:26:26.270 --> 00:26:29.480
Zeus, forgive us for these affronts

441
00:26:26.270 --> 00:26:29.480
and protect us.

442
00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:34.310
And you still believe

443
00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:34.310
they're going to help?

444
00:26:35.020 --> 00:26:36.440
This is suicide.

445
00:26:36.610 --> 00:26:38.940
MAN 1:

446
00:26:36.610 --> 00:26:38.940
And the shields. Come on, boys.

447
00:26:39.110 --> 00:26:41.160
MAN 2:

448
00:26:39.110 --> 00:26:41.160
It's a lost cause.

449
00:26:41.320 --> 00:26:43.950
We've no chance, and you know it.

450
00:26:44.280 --> 00:26:48.160
Here's who you drew into this, Perseus.

451
00:26:44.280 --> 00:26:48.160
An honor guard.

452
00:26:49.460 --> 00:26:52.710
Young men who look good

453
00:26:49.460 --> 00:26:52.710
on a reviewing stand...

454
00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:56.590
...and old soldiers,

455
00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:56.590
heading towards retirement.

456
00:26:57.210 --> 00:26:59.420
Do you know what the Kraken is?

457
00:27:00.720 --> 00:27:04.890
The Kraken is the end of us.

458
00:27:00.720 --> 00:27:04.890
A colossal, elemental beast.

459
00:27:05.050 --> 00:27:07.930
It doesn't think. It doesn't feel.

460
00:27:05.050 --> 00:27:07.930
Even the gods fear it.

461
00:27:08.100 --> 00:27:12.520
-And you, you're going to kill it?

462
00:27:08.100 --> 00:27:12.520
-Don't come.

463
00:27:13.060 --> 00:27:16.270
-I don't need your help.

464
00:27:13.060 --> 00:27:16.270
-Of course not.

465
00:27:17.230 --> 00:27:19.320
You're the son of Zeus.

466
00:27:20.070 --> 00:27:21.990
-But we have orders.

467
00:27:20.070 --> 00:27:21.990
MAN 3: Come, we need to leave!

468
00:27:22.150 --> 00:27:27.030
Gentlemen, may our journey be long,

469
00:27:22.150 --> 00:27:27.030
filled with agony and torment...

470
00:27:27.200 --> 00:27:30.120
...and may we all complain about it

471
00:27:27.200 --> 00:27:30.120
bitterly as old men.

472
00:27:30.290 --> 00:27:33.330
-So what should we bring?

473
00:27:30.290 --> 00:27:33.330
-Bring everything.

474
00:27:37.590 --> 00:27:40.130
What makes you think the witches

475
00:27:37.590 --> 00:27:40.130
will tell us anything?

476
00:27:40.300 --> 00:27:43.550
Oh, they'll tell us, or I'll kill them too.

477
00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:47.720
[WHIRRING]

478
00:27:48.600 --> 00:27:50.390
MAN 4:

479
00:27:48.600 --> 00:27:50.390
Come on. Let's go, boys.

480
00:27:51.770 --> 00:27:53.940
-What is this?

481
00:27:51.770 --> 00:27:53.940
-Just leave it.

482
00:27:58.610 --> 00:28:02.280
MAN: Don't leave us

483
00:27:58.610 --> 00:28:02.280
to the mercy of the gods! Please.

484
00:28:02.440 --> 00:28:05.030
WOMAN 1:

485
00:28:02.440 --> 00:28:05.030
Don't go. Please stay!

486
00:28:07.070 --> 00:28:10.040
Stay here. Please? Please? Help us.

487
00:28:12.200 --> 00:28:14.870
WOMAN 2: You're just going to

488
00:28:12.200 --> 00:28:14.870
make the gods angrier. Please.

489
00:28:15.040 --> 00:28:17.130
Just sacrifice the princess!

490
00:28:17.290 --> 00:28:20.300
Watch your mouth! Stay back. Stay back!

491
00:28:20.460 --> 00:28:22.090
You'd think they might be thankful.

492
00:28:23.090 --> 00:28:24.340
WOMAN 3:

493
00:28:23.090 --> 00:28:24.340
You cannot desert us!

494
00:28:24.510 --> 00:28:26.300
Maybe they're tired of being thankful.

495
00:28:27.430 --> 00:28:28.970
OZAL:

496
00:28:27.430 --> 00:28:28.970
Good news!

497
00:28:29.140 --> 00:28:31.220
My brother and I have decided...

498
00:28:31.390 --> 00:28:35.140
-...to accompany you on your journey.

499
00:28:31.390 --> 00:28:35.140
-We have enough strangers here.

500
00:28:35.310 --> 00:28:38.150
We can be of great help to you,

501
00:28:35.310 --> 00:28:38.150
trust me. You'll need us.

502
00:28:38.310 --> 00:28:40.070
I need soldiers, not hunters.

503
00:28:41.480 --> 00:28:45.200
Which one of your soldiers

504
00:28:41.480 --> 00:28:45.200
knows how to cut the impenetrable skin...

505
00:28:45.360 --> 00:28:46.820
...of the Nemean lion?

506
00:28:46.990 --> 00:28:51.030
Which one of them knows the soft points

507
00:28:46.990 --> 00:28:51.030
on a centaur's armor?

508
00:28:51.200 --> 00:28:56.460
Which one of them knows which jugular

509
00:28:51.200 --> 00:28:56.460
to slice on a five-headed Hydra?

510
00:28:57.210 --> 00:29:00.000
-The middle one.

511
00:28:57.210 --> 00:29:00.000
-The middle one. Good guess.

512
00:29:00.170 --> 00:29:02.550
My brother and I, we know how to kill.

513
00:29:02.710 --> 00:29:04.340
-We enjoy it.

514
00:29:02.710 --> 00:29:04.340
-If you can keep up...

515
00:29:04.510 --> 00:29:06.430
...and you don't mind dying, come along.

516
00:29:07.470 --> 00:29:09.680
It is death who should be afraid of us.

517
00:29:57.480 --> 00:29:59.440
HADES:

518
00:29:57.480 --> 00:29:59.440
King Acrisius.

519
00:29:59.600 --> 00:30:02.230
CALIBOS:

520
00:29:59.600 --> 00:30:02.230
There is no Acrisius.

521
00:30:02.560 --> 00:30:04.610
Just Calibos.

522
00:30:12.490 --> 00:30:14.660
HADES:

523
00:30:12.490 --> 00:30:14.660
We have an enemy in common.

524
00:30:15.540 --> 00:30:17.910
-Zeus.

525
00:30:21.210 --> 00:30:23.250
HADES:

526
00:30:21.210 --> 00:30:23.250
My brother.

527
00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:27.130
CALIBOS:

528
00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:27.130
What do you want from me?

529
00:30:27.300 --> 00:30:31.720
Zeus' seed in your wife survived.

530
00:30:31.970 --> 00:30:34.510
The child of your shame.

531
00:30:35.720 --> 00:30:37.310
Perseus.

532
00:30:37.470 --> 00:30:38.980
CALIBOS:

533
00:30:37.470 --> 00:30:38.980
He lives?

534
00:30:39.560 --> 00:30:42.060
You murdered your wife for nothing.

535
00:30:42.690 --> 00:30:48.190
Now Perseus hurls himself

536
00:30:42.690 --> 00:30:48.190
from Argos to destroy me.

537
00:30:48.780 --> 00:30:50.490
He must die.

538
00:30:50.650 --> 00:30:55.240
-What would you have me do?

539
00:30:50.650 --> 00:30:55.240
-Zeus must think I serve him...

540
00:30:55.410 --> 00:30:58.200
...but I am growing stronger.

541
00:30:58.830 --> 00:31:02.120
Until I possess my full power...

542
00:31:04.130 --> 00:31:07.460
...you will be my weapon.

543
00:31:09.670 --> 00:31:11.130
Come.

544
00:31:41.200 --> 00:31:42.710
Use this.

545
00:31:43.830 --> 00:31:46.790
Kill Perseus for me.

546
00:31:47.210 --> 00:31:51.050
And I'll destroy Zeus for you.

547
00:31:51.210 --> 00:31:53.220
I serve you.

548
00:31:53.380 --> 00:31:55.590
The boy will die.

549
00:32:00.680 --> 00:32:02.480
MAN 1:

550
00:32:00.680 --> 00:32:02.480
How far is it?

551
00:32:02.640 --> 00:32:04.640
MAN 2:

552
00:32:02.640 --> 00:32:04.640
Four days to the witches.

553
00:32:04.810 --> 00:32:08.230
MAN 3:

554
00:32:04.810 --> 00:32:08.230
Four days? I'm tired already.

555
00:32:11.440 --> 00:32:13.610
Here, use this.

556
00:32:18.530 --> 00:32:20.410
Would you like us to wait?

557
00:32:21.290 --> 00:32:23.160
BELO:

558
00:32:21.290 --> 00:32:23.160
Oops.

559
00:32:40.060 --> 00:32:43.980
[BLOWING]

560
00:33:09.920 --> 00:33:11.880
[BLOWING]

561
00:33:19.760 --> 00:33:21.350
KUCUK:

562
00:33:19.760 --> 00:33:21.350
You really are a fisherman.

563
00:33:21.510 --> 00:33:23.470
You should've seen my father.

564
00:33:23.930 --> 00:33:25.430
You.

565
00:33:26.020 --> 00:33:27.730
Bring your weapon.

566
00:33:37.400 --> 00:33:39.030
Have you handled a sword before?

567
00:33:39.200 --> 00:33:41.320
-There's been no need.

568
00:33:39.200 --> 00:33:41.320
-I see.

569
00:33:41.990 --> 00:33:43.990
Left foot forward.

570
00:33:47.290 --> 00:33:50.750
Your motions should be fluid.

571
00:33:51.420 --> 00:33:53.630
The weapon is a part of you.

572
00:33:55.960 --> 00:33:57.170
Like the sting on a wasp.

