00:58:03.600 --> 00:58:06.770
Anything of flesh is killed by her gaze.

861
00:58:06.930 --> 00:58:10.770
ENYO: Killed by her.

862
00:58:06.930 --> 00:58:10.770
-Her prison lies across the River Styx...

863
00:58:10.940 --> 00:58:14.020
-...at the edge of the underworld.

864
00:58:10.940 --> 00:58:14.020
ENYO: A Titan against a Titan.

865
00:58:14.190 --> 00:58:16.940
DRACO: She's no use against the Kraken.

866
00:58:14.190 --> 00:58:16.940
We can't control her.

867
00:58:18.610 --> 00:58:19.900
Then we take her head.

868
00:58:20.530 --> 00:58:24.030
ENYO: Clever boy.

869
00:58:20.530 --> 00:58:24.030
-Now the eye. Give us the eye.

870
00:58:24.200 --> 00:58:25.530
-The eye.

871
00:58:30.710 --> 00:58:31.830
Where is it?

872
00:58:36.460 --> 00:58:39.670
But wait. There's more.

873
00:58:36.460 --> 00:58:39.670
Don't you want to know more?

874
00:58:39.840 --> 00:58:41.090
Perseus, no.

875
00:58:42.510 --> 00:58:44.260
DEINO: Tell him.

876
00:58:42.510 --> 00:58:44.260
PEMPHREDO: Tell him.

877
00:58:44.430 --> 00:58:45.470
What?

878
00:58:45.640 --> 00:58:48.220
ENYO:

879
00:58:45.640 --> 00:58:48.220
Your journey does not end well.

880
00:58:49.270 --> 00:58:51.140
Fate has spoken.

881
00:58:54.440 --> 00:58:57.650
You will die, son of Zeus!

882
00:59:00.280 --> 00:59:01.700
It's a lie. Come.

883
00:59:02.570 --> 00:59:03.820
Written as history.

884
00:59:06.780 --> 00:59:07.990
Perseus.

885
00:59:08.160 --> 00:59:11.250
You will die.

886
00:59:30.770 --> 00:59:32.270
EUSEBIOS:

887
00:59:30.770 --> 00:59:32.270
Why are the Djinn leaving us?

888
00:59:32.430 --> 00:59:35.400
IXAS: They believe we will all die.

889
00:59:32.430 --> 00:59:35.400
It's the prophecy.

890
00:59:57.500 --> 00:59:58.540
Who are you?

891
01:00:07.010 --> 01:00:11.310
Well, you can call me "Father"...

892
01:00:12.270 --> 01:00:15.020
-...if you wish.

893
01:00:12.270 --> 01:00:15.020
-My father's dead.

894
01:00:15.600 --> 01:00:17.190
He was killed by a god.

895
01:00:17.350 --> 01:00:20.230
An unfortunate casualty

896
01:00:17.350 --> 01:00:20.230
in a war men brought on themselves.

897
01:00:20.900 --> 01:00:24.650
Men didn't murder my family.

898
01:00:20.900 --> 01:00:24.650
Your brother did.

899
01:00:25.570 --> 01:00:27.240
You heard the witches' prophesy.

900
01:00:27.410 --> 01:00:29.910
You will not defeat the Kraken,

901
01:00:27.410 --> 01:00:29.910
much less Hades.

902
01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:34.250
If you continue this journey,

903
01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:34.250
you will die, and Argos will still fall.

904
01:00:34.410 --> 01:00:36.080
If you're so sure, why are you here?

905
01:00:36.250 --> 01:00:38.040
To offer you sanctuary.

906
01:00:38.210 --> 01:00:42.000
Your blood is mine, Perseus,

907
01:00:38.210 --> 01:00:42.000
and that makes you a god.

908
01:00:42.170 --> 01:00:44.840
It's time you came to Olympus

909
01:00:42.170 --> 01:00:44.840
and started living like one.

910
01:00:45.010 --> 01:00:47.970
Rather die in the mud with those men

911
01:00:45.010 --> 01:00:47.970
than live forever as a god.

912
01:00:48.140 --> 01:00:49.510
You foolish boy.

913
01:00:49.680 --> 01:00:52.680
Man's entire existence

914
01:00:49.680 --> 01:00:52.680
is a gift of my grace.

915
01:00:52.850 --> 01:00:54.270
For someone who created man...

916
01:00:54.430 --> 01:00:56.810
...you don't know much about us.

917
01:00:57.480 --> 01:00:59.440
We live...

918
01:00:59.770 --> 01:01:02.360
...we fight and we die...

919
01:01:02.520 --> 01:01:05.240
...for each other, not for you.

920
01:01:06.950 --> 01:01:08.610
Tell Hades I'll see him soon.

921
01:01:09.910 --> 01:01:12.870
-I will not make this offer again.

922
01:01:09.910 --> 01:01:12.870
-Good.

923
01:01:13.040 --> 01:01:14.950
Because I'd hate to refuse you twice.

924
01:01:15.120 --> 01:01:17.160
Perseus.

925
01:01:17.330 --> 01:01:18.920
Wait.

926
01:01:25.630 --> 01:01:28.090
It's expensive where you're going.

927
01:01:52.240 --> 01:01:54.700
Kucuk fashioned this shield

928
01:01:52.240 --> 01:01:54.700
from the Scorpioch.

929
01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:58.910
Stronger and lighter than any metal.

930
01:01:59.420 --> 01:02:01.420
Very rare and high-quality item.

931
01:02:05.960 --> 01:02:07.760
We can fight anywhere...

932
01:02:09.840 --> 01:02:12.180
...but not in the underworld.

933
01:02:13.350 --> 01:02:14.890
Yeah.

934
01:02:19.480 --> 01:02:20.980
Good luck, fisherman.

935
01:02:35.700 --> 01:02:37.620
We all heard what the witches said.

936
01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:41.290
But we can prove them wrong.

937
01:02:42.920 --> 01:02:44.290
I need your help.

938
01:02:55.390 --> 01:02:57.260
It wasn't the gods

939
01:02:55.390 --> 01:02:57.260
that saved me up there.

940
01:02:59.810 --> 01:03:02.140
If you believe that we have a chance.

941
01:03:06.110 --> 01:03:08.320
I never liked Argos much anyway.

942
01:03:13.570 --> 01:03:15.280
IO:

943
01:03:13.570 --> 01:03:15.280
I know the way.

944
01:03:20.200 --> 01:03:23.420
Then we go to the underworld.

945
01:03:20.200 --> 01:03:23.420
We kill Medusa.

946
01:03:23.580 --> 01:03:24.920
[GROWLS]

947
01:04:13.510 --> 01:04:17.300
SOLON: Now what?

948
01:04:13.510 --> 01:04:17.300
-We wait for Charon.

949
01:04:18.350 --> 01:04:20.060
Charon only ferries the dead.

950
01:04:21.100 --> 01:04:22.640
Any volunteers?

951
01:04:32.820 --> 01:04:34.030
Heads we swim.

952
01:04:59.760 --> 01:05:01.850
A bribe for the ferryman.

953
01:05:32.050 --> 01:05:34.420
[SPEAKS IN DJINN LANGUAGE]

954
01:05:57.700 --> 01:05:59.410
So, what happens when we get there?

955
01:06:00.240 --> 01:06:01.620
Just another beast to kill.

956
01:06:02.410 --> 01:06:04.040
A beast?

957
01:06:04.750 --> 01:06:07.330
Medusa was beautiful once.

958
01:06:07.500 --> 01:06:10.330
So beautiful as to tempt Poseidon.

959
01:06:10.500 --> 01:06:12.710
When he came for her...

960
01:06:12.880 --> 01:06:17.090
...she ran to Athena's temple thinking

961
01:06:12.880 --> 01:06:17.090
that the goddess would protect her.

962
01:06:17.800 --> 01:06:19.300
She didn't.

963
01:06:20.590 --> 01:06:22.810
Poseidon took her on the cold floor.

964
01:06:23.600 --> 01:06:25.980
She prayed to Athena for comfort...

965
01:06:26.140 --> 01:06:28.520
...but the goddess felt nothing

966
01:06:26.140 --> 01:06:28.520
but disgust.

967
01:06:28.690 --> 01:06:32.360
She made sure

968
01:06:28.690 --> 01:06:32.360
no one would ever want Medusa again.

969
01:06:32.520 --> 01:06:36.820
One look at the creature she has become

970
01:06:32.520 --> 01:06:36.820
will turn any living thing to stone.

971
01:06:37.610 --> 01:06:41.320
I cannot assist you there.

972
01:06:37.610 --> 01:06:41.320
A curse prevents me.

973
01:06:42.450 --> 01:06:46.450
It was Athena's one bit of solace to Medusa

974
01:06:42.450 --> 01:06:46.450
so that Medusa would never harm a woman.

975
01:06:47.620 --> 01:06:50.170
Only men are allowed in the temple.

976
01:06:51.040 --> 01:06:53.790
Though no man has ever made it out.

977
01:07:25.830 --> 01:07:27.540
[GRUNTING]

978
01:07:27.700 --> 01:07:30.830
Medusa's got a tail

979
01:07:27.700 --> 01:07:30.830
and that's how she'll use it.

980
01:07:32.040 --> 01:07:33.540
Listen.

981
01:07:34.330 --> 01:07:36.880
Hear her muscles coil.

982
01:07:37.550 --> 01:07:39.970
Smell her skin.

983
01:07:40.630 --> 01:07:43.340
Feel her hunger in your gut.

984
01:07:44.640 --> 01:07:46.140
Medusa's killed you twice now.

985
01:07:47.390 --> 01:07:51.940
Do you think she'll hand you her head?

986
01:07:47.390 --> 01:07:51.940
She won't be gracious about it.

987
01:07:52.390 --> 01:07:55.810
One look in her eyes

988
01:07:52.390 --> 01:07:55.810
and you'll turn to stone.

989
01:07:57.690 --> 01:07:59.190
Good.

990
01:08:02.990 --> 01:08:06.370
-Try not to enjoy this so much.

991
01:08:02.990 --> 01:08:06.370
-I'm trying to help you live.

992
01:08:08.410 --> 01:08:09.700
Don't look at me.

993
01:08:30.270 --> 01:08:32.140
Ease your storm.

994
01:08:39.730 --> 01:08:40.940
[CLEARS THROAT]

995
01:08:41.110 --> 01:08:42.820
SOLON:

996
01:08:41.110 --> 01:08:42.820
We're nearing Medusa's lair.

997
01:08:59.210 --> 01:09:02.340
I never thought I could reach this place.

998
01:09:04.260 --> 01:09:05.550
Who'd you lose?

999
01:09:12.270 --> 01:09:14.020
My daughter.

1000
01:09:16.100 --> 01:09:18.730
Taken away on her 16th birthday.

1001
01:09:19.980 --> 01:09:22.230
Dragged down here.

1002
01:09:22.690 --> 01:09:25.110
I have a feeling I'll see her soon.

1003
01:09:28.990 --> 01:09:32.700
You brought us this far.

1004
01:09:28.990 --> 01:09:32.700
Let's go the rest of the way.

1005
01:09:52.510 --> 01:09:54.930
-How many coins did you get, Perseus?

1006
01:09:52.510 --> 01:09:54.930
-Just the one.

1007
01:10:21.250 --> 01:10:23.250
I only knew one great man in my life.

1008
01:10:26.260 --> 01:10:27.800
My father.

1009
01:10:30.800 --> 01:10:32.010
Now I know four more.

1010
01:10:35.850 --> 01:10:36.890
And a woman.

1011
01:10:39.940 --> 01:10:41.360
And whatever the hell you are.

1012
01:10:46.110 --> 01:10:48.200
I know we're all afraid.

1013
01:10:48.490 --> 01:10:49.910
But my father told me:

1014
01:10:50.070 --> 01:10:53.120
Someday someone was gonna have to

1015
01:10:50.070 --> 01:10:53.120
take a stand.

1016
01:10:53.620 --> 01:10:56.790
Someday someone

1017
01:10:53.620 --> 01:10:56.790
was gonna have to say, "Enough."

1018
01:10:59.710 --> 01:11:00.920
This could be that day.

1019
01:11:02.960 --> 01:11:04.750
Trust your senses.

1020
01:11:04.920 --> 01:11:07.090
And don't look this bitch in the eye.

1021
01:11:38.200 --> 01:11:41.710
-Doesn't really inspire confidence.

1022
01:11:38.200 --> 01:11:41.710
-Quiet.

1023
01:11:42.210 --> 01:11:44.460
-Listen.

1024
01:11:42.210 --> 01:11:44.460
PERSEUS: Eusebios.

1025
01:11:44.630 --> 01:11:46.420
Keep your eyes down.

1026
01:11:56.310 --> 01:11:59.020
[MEDUSA LAUGHING]

1027
01:12:08.730 --> 01:12:09.940
Here we go.

1028
01:12:15.200 --> 01:12:17.740
[YELLING]

1029
01:12:20.660 --> 01:12:22.710
Solon!

1030
01:12:26.840 --> 01:12:28.170
Keep going!

1031
01:12:30.630 --> 01:12:32.300
Flank her.

1032
01:12:36.300 --> 01:12:38.970
-Draco.

1033
01:12:36.300 --> 01:12:38.970
-Go!

1034
01:12:40.020 --> 01:12:41.480
Eusebios, follow me.

1035
01:12:46.900 --> 01:12:48.190
Hang on!

1036
01:12:48.570 --> 01:12:51.070
[SPEAKS IN DJINN LANGUAGE]

1037
01:12:54.610 --> 01:12:56.780
[PERSEUS YELLS]

1038
01:13:01.200 --> 01:13:03.330
[GRUNTING]

1039
01:13:11.760 --> 01:13:14.670
[MEDUSA LAUGHING]

1040
01:13:21.680 --> 01:13:23.390
IXAS:

1041
01:13:21.680 --> 01:13:23.390
Eusebios.

1042
01:13:25.940 --> 01:13:28.230
Remember what Perseus said.

1043
01:13:34.530 --> 01:13:36.320
Eyes down.

1044
01:13:50.880 --> 01:13:52.420
Ixas, no.

1045
01:13:56.880 --> 01:13:58.800
[YELLS]

1046
01:13:59.050 --> 01:14:00.550
Eyes down.

1047
01:14:05.390 --> 01:14:07.940
Where are you?

1048
01:14:10.060 --> 01:14:11.900
Where are you?

1049
01:14:20.370 --> 01:14:22.120
PERSEUS:

1050
01:14:20.370 --> 01:14:22.120
Eusebios.

1051
01:14:23.330 --> 01:14:25.700
[MEDUSA LAUGHING]

1052
01:14:28.370 --> 01:14:29.790
Go!

1053
01:14:44.680 --> 01:14:46.310
Wait here.

1054
01:14:47.850 --> 01:14:48.940
I'll lure her out.

1055
01:14:50.230 --> 01:14:51.900
Get ready.

1056
01:14:52.060 --> 01:14:53.820
[PERSEUS YELLING]

1057
01:15:39.240 --> 01:15:40.320
Now!

1058
01:15:57.590 --> 01:16:00.380
Together.

1059
01:16:31.200 --> 01:16:32.370
[YELLING]

1060
01:16:42.420 --> 01:16:44.840
Let them know men did this.

1061
01:18:05.300 --> 01:18:07.590
[SCREAMS]

1062
01:18:10.470 --> 01:18:12.350
Just you and me, son of Zeus.

1063
01:18:16.140 --> 01:18:17.810
[YELLING]

1064
01:19:22.380 --> 01:19:23.880
Perseus.

1065
01:19:24.840 --> 01:19:26.590
Don't become one of them.

1066
01:19:42.400 --> 01:19:44.230
Io, I'm here.

1067
01:19:46.610 --> 01:19:48.610
There's no time.

1068
01:19:51.570 --> 01:19:53.240
The eclipse.

1069
01:19:54.530 --> 01:19:57.910
Perseus, you must go before it's too late.

1070
01:20:02.790 --> 01:20:04.380
I'm not going anywhere.

1071
01:20:05.590 --> 01:20:07.670
My fate is certain.

1072
01:20:07.840 --> 01:20:11.170
But the fate of Argos

1073
01:20:07.840 --> 01:20:11.170
is still in your hands.

1074
01:20:12.090 --> 01:20:14.430
All my life you've been there.

1075
01:20:15.600 --> 01:20:16.760
You never left me.

1076
01:20:18.850 --> 01:20:20.020
I can't leave you.

1077
01:20:21.810 --> 01:20:24.310
This part of the journey

1078
01:20:21.810 --> 01:20:24.310
you must do alone.

1079
01:20:25.020 --> 01:20:26.440
Perseus...

1080
01:20:26.610 --> 01:20:28.940
...you're not just part man, part god...

1081
01:20:31.150 --> 01:20:33.320
...you're the best of both.

1082
01:20:38.830 --> 01:20:41.200
Everything will be all right.

1083
01:21:37.010 --> 01:21:38.550
Brother.

1084
01:21:39.180 --> 01:21:42.680
It is time for the mortals to pay.

1085
01:21:45.350 --> 01:21:47.730
My child waits to do your will.

1086
01:21:58.240 --> 01:21:59.990
ZEUS:

1087
01:21:58.240 --> 01:21:59.990
Leave us.

1088
01:22:07.040 --> 01:22:09.290
Release the Kraken!

1089
01:22:36.900 --> 01:22:39.990
The Kraken comes now!

1090
01:22:40.450 --> 01:22:44.790
Our suffering ends

1091
01:22:40.450 --> 01:22:44.790
when the beast is sated!

1092
01:22:45.370 --> 01:22:47.370
Will it take us...

1093
01:22:48.160 --> 01:22:51.290
...or will it take Andromeda?

1094
01:22:51.460 --> 01:22:53.540
CROWD:

1095
01:22:51.460 --> 01:22:53.540
Andromeda!

1096
01:22:56.760 --> 01:22:58.510
ANDROMEDA:

1097
01:22:56.760 --> 01:22:58.510
It's my name they're calling.

1098
01:22:59.680 --> 01:23:01.930
This cannot continue.

1099
01:23:12.360 --> 01:23:14.490
MAN 1: Stay back!

1100
01:23:12.360 --> 01:23:14.490
MAN 2: Stay back!

1101
01:23:44.520 --> 01:23:47.270
Look! The Kraken! Help us!

1102
01:23:59.070 --> 01:24:01.490
[CROWD YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

1103
01:24:14.300 --> 01:24:16.380
KEPHEUS:

1104
01:24:14.300 --> 01:24:16.380
Andromeda!

1105
01:24:18.880 --> 01:24:23.890
Hades, we sacrifice our princess

1106
01:24:18.880 --> 01:24:23.890
in your name.

1107
01:24:29.440 --> 01:24:32.690
It comes, brothers and sisters!

1108
01:24:39.450 --> 01:24:42.280
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

1109
01:25:03.640 --> 01:25:05.260
Argos has fallen.

1110
01:25:06.350 --> 01:25:09.020
Do you feel stronger, brother?

1111
01:25:09.640 --> 01:25:12.400
You thought the Kraken

1112
01:25:09.640 --> 01:25:12.400
would bring you their prayers.

1113
01:25:12.900 --> 01:25:17.150
But the Kraken is my child.

1114
01:25:12.900 --> 01:25:17.150
It feeds only me.

1115
01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:20.700
I command Olympus.

1116
01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:20.700
Remember who you serve.

1117
01:25:21.360 --> 01:25:23.610
I serve myself.

1118
01:25:23.780 --> 01:25:26.910
I have since you cheated me.

1119
01:25:28.160 --> 01:25:30.370
You sent me to the underworld

1120
01:25:28.160 --> 01:25:30.370
to be hated...

1121
01:25:30.540 --> 01:25:32.620
...while you basked in their love.

1122
01:25:33.750 --> 01:25:35.290
We need the love of humans.

1123
01:25:35.460 --> 01:25:37.380
No, you need it.

1124
01:25:37.550 --> 01:25:39.170
I survive on their fear.

1125
01:25:39.760 --> 01:25:41.920
Your reign is over, brother Zeus.

1126
01:25:42.090 --> 01:25:46.220
You'll watch while my blessed avenger

1127
01:25:42.090 --> 01:25:46.220
devours their hopes.

1128
01:25:46.390 --> 01:25:49.430
And then finally you'll know my pain.

1129
01:25:49.970 --> 01:25:53.230
There is still a demigod in Argos...

1130
01:25:53.390 --> 01:25:55.100
...brother.

1131
01:25:59.780 --> 01:26:00.830
Perseus.

1132
01:26:34.150 --> 01:26:36.440
The bag! Come on!

1133
01:26:48.960 --> 01:26:50.630
Hyah!

1134
01:28:07.080 --> 01:28:10.330
KUCUK:

1135
01:28:07.080 --> 01:28:10.330
Hey, fisherman!

1136
01:28:11.960 --> 01:28:13.250
[LAUGHING]

1137
01:29:15.310 --> 01:29:17.020
Come on!

1138
01:29:17.360 --> 01:29:19.480
[PERSEUS YELLS]

1139
01:30:21.510 --> 01:30:23.390
No!

1140
01:30:45.080 --> 01:30:46.620
[SCREAMS]

1141
01:31:10.480 --> 01:31:12.270
I'm a god.

1142
01:31:12.440 --> 01:31:14.150
I will live forever.

1143
01:31:14.320 --> 01:31:15.780
But not here.

1144
01:32:41.530 --> 01:32:44.030
ANDROMEDA:

1145
01:32:41.530 --> 01:32:44.030
The boats are coming for us.

1146
01:32:48.990 --> 01:32:50.410
For you. Not for me.

1147
01:32:51.870 --> 01:32:53.500
You won't stay, will you?

1148
01:32:55.170 --> 01:32:57.040
Perseus, Argos needs a ruler.

1149
01:32:57.920 --> 01:32:59.250
I cannot be a king.

1150
01:33:00.250 --> 01:33:02.090
I serve you better as a man.

1151
01:33:03.340 --> 01:33:05.800
You'll make a fine queen for them.

1152
01:33:45.810 --> 01:33:48.600
ZEUS:

1153
01:33:45.810 --> 01:33:48.600
Olympus owes you a debt of gratitude.

1154
01:33:50.270 --> 01:33:51.900
As do I.

1155
01:33:52.060 --> 01:33:53.690
Hades lives.

1156
01:33:54.150 --> 01:33:56.440
He's just sent back to the underworld.

1157
01:33:56.610 --> 01:33:58.570
Biding his time, no doubt.

1158
01:33:58.740 --> 01:34:02.450
Waiting for men to grow weak,

1159
01:33:58.740 --> 01:34:02.450
and in their weakness, he grows stronger.

1160
01:34:03.280 --> 01:34:05.580
It's mankind who holds the key

1161
01:34:03.280 --> 01:34:05.580
to Hades' rise.

1162
01:34:05.740 --> 01:34:06.790
It always was.

1163
01:34:06.950 --> 01:34:09.330
So we'll see him again.

1164
01:34:09.960 --> 01:34:11.210
Yes.

1165
01:34:11.370 --> 01:34:14.170
But now the world knows

1166
01:34:11.370 --> 01:34:14.170
a man can stop him.

1167
01:34:14.960 --> 01:34:17.800
Of course, you had some help.

1168
01:34:17.960 --> 01:34:21.130
A sword, the Pegasus....

1169
01:34:22.090 --> 01:34:26.760
I wanted men to worship us again,

1170
01:34:22.090 --> 01:34:26.760
but I didn't want it to cost me a son.

1171
01:34:29.020 --> 01:34:30.310
That's almost human of you.

1172
01:34:30.480 --> 01:34:34.270
I don't suppose you'll reconsider my offer

1173
01:34:30.480 --> 01:34:34.270
to take your place as one of us.

1174
01:34:38.860 --> 01:34:41.280
I've got everything I need right here.

1175
01:34:42.070 --> 01:34:43.950
You may not want to be a god, Perseus...

1176
01:34:44.110 --> 01:34:47.660
...but after feats like yours,

1177
01:34:44.110 --> 01:34:47.660
men will worship you.

1178
01:34:49.040 --> 01:34:50.910
Be good to them.

1179
01:34:51.080 --> 01:34:53.420
Be better than we were.

1180
01:34:54.670 --> 01:34:58.000
And if you insist on continuing

1181
01:34:54.670 --> 01:34:58.000
this mundane human existence...

1182
01:34:58.170 --> 01:34:59.960
...I won't have you do it alone.

1183
01:35:01.300 --> 01:35:02.880
You're the son of Zeus, after all.

1184
01:46:03.340 --> 01:46:05.340
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
